<H3> <TI>   Government Forces Reportedly Advance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Forces Reportedly Advance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0206024194 Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA in Cambodian 2 
Jun 94 pp 1, 2 </F>

<F P=103> BK0206024194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] According to a report dated 30 May from the 
front line, the combined forces of the Royal Government have 
already reached the Chi Neang point on Route 10, 18 km east of 
Pailin. No clashes have been reported, and the government 
troops, which seem to be very vigilant at this point in time, 
have not yet overrun the area. 
  The report further says that the plateau Phnum Veng on Route 
10 near Chineang is also being surrounded by government forces. 
  A senior Army officer said the government forces' advance 
has 
not encountered any heavy attacks and that the smooth headway 
indicated that the Khmer Royal Armed Forces are on the alert and 
have never forgotten their recent shameful defeats. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

