<DOCNO> FBIS4-27719 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas108_h_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-108 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Brunei Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CNN NEWS Report on Bosnia Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNN NEWS Report on Bosnia Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Told to Focus on Injustice </H4>

<F P=102> BK0406150094 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in Malay 
1300 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Malay </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] International media, especially the Cable News 
Network [CNN], should focus its coverage on the injustice the 
Bosnian people face, instead of making false reports on the 
issue. Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak said the 
media should see the injustice that prevails there, namely the 
continued arms embargo faced by the Bosnians, while Serb 
terrorists continue to receive arms from Belgrade. This is the 
current injustice the Bosnians face and the media must fight 
against it. 
  The minister was speaking to reporters after he met local 
UMNO [United Malays National Organization] leaders in Johor 
Baharu today. He was commenting on a CNN report, the effect of 
which was that Malaysia had been providing arms to Bosnia. The 
minister also reiterated Prime Minister Dr. Mahathir's denial of 
the report. He said he could not understand why CNN carried the 
incorrect report. He added that 50 million ringgit has been 
allocated to upgrade military camps nationwide. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

