<F P=100> Brunei Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CNN NEWS Report on Bosnia Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNN NEWS Report on Bosnia Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    CNN Agrees To Correct Report </H4>

<F P=102> BK0606045394 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0332 GMT 6 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0606045394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, Jun 6 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- Cable News 
Network (CNN) of the United States has agreed to carry a denial 
of its report that Malaysia supplied arms to Bosnian Muslims, 
Information Minister Mohamed Rahmat said Sunday. 
  The television station would also contact the Malaysian 
Embassy in Washington to rectify the error, he told reporters in 
southern Johor state. 
  CNN had recently carried a report saying that Malaysia had 
supplied light weapons to the Muslim army in war-torn 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Mohamed said the government did not want to pick a quarrel 
with the CNN over the report but hoped that the western media 
including CNN would be fair and accurate in their reporting, 
particularly on Malaysia. 
  We only wanted a clarification from CNN... But they said 
they 
will carry a denial, which is very good as we want fair 
reporting, he said, adding that CNN had written to him a few 
days ago. 

</TEXT>

