<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary Says War Only Way To Achieve Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commentary Says War Only Way To Achieve Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0406112694 Phnom Penh KAOH SANTEPHEAP in Cambodian 1-2 Jun 
94 p 1, 4 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh KAOH SANTEPHEAP </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Unattributed commentary: "Both the Khmer Rouge and Their 
Newspapers Must Be Eliminated"] 
  [Text] Both the Khmer Rouge elements and their newspapers in 
Phnom Penh have continued to claim that the government [RG] is a 
warmonger and does not want peace. Now, it has been shown 
clearly, through the roundtable meeting, who the warmongers are 
and who does and does not want peace. 
  Three planeloads of government officials went to attend the 
meeting as if to beg the Khmer Rouge for peace, but the Khmer 
Rouge refused to accept peace through negotiation. 
  The government accepted an unconditional cease-fire in place 
to begin at noon on 15 June before holding any further talks. 
But Khmer Rouge leader Khieu Samphan rejected it, claiming that 
foreign troops are still in Cambodia. At the same time, he 
demanded the dismantling of all national institutions from the 
monarchy, government, and National Assembly down to village 
committees. 
  Should we agree to dismantle the national institutions that 
we have built with the assistance of the international community? 
  Both the Cambodians, who own this country, and the 
international community will certainly not agree to this. 
  Therefore, we have only one alternative, that is, to 
continue 
the war to smash the Khmer Rouge, which is just a paper tiger. 
  We have said earlier that only by using war against war can 
we achieve peace. That is, if the roundtable fails due to the 
Khmer Rouge. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

