<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister on Cost of Warships </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister on Cost of Warships </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0406083594 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense and Security Minister Edi Sudrajat considers 
the purchase of 39 former East German warships at $1.1 billion 
expensive because the cost could be reduced to $300 million. 
The Indonesian Navy's estimate of $300 million for the warships 
covers the cost of the warships, which also includes repairs, 
voyage expenses, and expenses for port facilities. 
  During his briefing in Jakarta today, Minister Edi Sudrajat 
urged the finance minister to reconsider the current $1.1 
billion allocation because previous finance department 
allocations for the warships had been based on the Indonesian 
Navy's estimates of $300 million. Minister Edi Sudrajat said 
the Navy had taken into consideration the age of the warships, 
which were constructed for war purposes. 

</TEXT>

