<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Stresses No Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Stresses No Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0606075694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0700 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0606075694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Information Minister Harmoko has stated that 
President Suharto will not issue a presidential decree on 
foreign investment in mass media although such investment is 
permitted under Government Regulation No. 20/1994. Speaking to 
reporters after meeting the president at Merdeka Palace this 
afternoon, the information minister urged the general public to 
stop making a fuss over the matter because the president's 
policy is clear. Harmoko subsequently urged the general public 
to stop questioning Government Regulation No. 20, particularly 
the clause on possible foreign investment in mass media through 
joint ventures. 
  He also informed the head of state of the indefinite 
postponement of the Islamic Conference Organization information 
ministers conference. 

</TEXT>

