Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Premier, Delegation Visit Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Premier, Delegation Visit Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hailed by PASASON Editorial </H4>

<F P=102> BK0306145494 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0306145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial from 3 June PASASON: "Wholeheartedly Welcome the </F>
Premier of the DPRK Administrative Council"] 
  [Text] At the invitation of Comrade Khamtai Siphandon, 
prime minister of the Lao People's Democratic Republic, Comrade 
Kang Song-san, premier of the DPRK Administrative Council, will 
lead a delegation to pay an official friendship visit to the Lao 
People's Democratic Republic [LPDR] on 3 June. 
  Reacting to this event of great significance in the 
relations 
of profound friendship and close cooperation between Laos and 
Korea, the entire Lao people and Vientiane residents are 
extremely pleased to have the great honor and an opportunity to 
welcome Comrade Kang Song-san and his entourage right on Lao 
soil. They will bring the goodwill, friendship, and intimate 
brotherly affection from the fraternal Korean people to our Lao 
people. 
  The official friendship visit to our country by the premier 
of the DPRK Administrative Council and his delegation takes 
place after several delegations of Laos and Korea have exchanged 
visits with one another, especially the official friendship 
visit to the DPRK in December 1993 by our high-level party-state 
delegation headed by Comrade Khamtai Siphandon, which ended in 
glorious success. The visit by the DPRK premier clearly 
testifies to the development in the fine relations of friendship 
and close comradely solidarity between the two comrades who 
share common ideals and between the two parties, states, and 
peoples of Laos and Korea. These relations and solidarity have 
been nurtured by President Kim Il-song and President Kaysone 
Phomvihan and further strengthened to continuously bear fruit, 
thereby contributing to the strengthening of solidarity among 
the nations sharing similar ideals and to the building of peace, 
stability, and cooperation among the countries in the 
Asia-Pacific region and the world over. 
  The LPDR and the DPRK consistently have shared common 
objectives and ideals. The Lao and Korean peoples have 
maintained fine relations for a long time. They have 
consistently rendered support and assistance to one another. 
The relations and cooperation between the parties, states, and 
peoples of Laos and Korea have continuously been further 
strengthened. The relations and cooperation between the two 
countries, particularly in the economic field, have advanced, 
especially following the visit to the DPRK by Comrade Khamtai 
Siphandon last December. 
  The Lao people would like to take this opportunity to 
express 
our sincere thanks toward the fraternal Korean party, state, and 
people for having rendered assistance to us in the past. We 
pledge to give consistent support and solidarity to the 
fraternal Korean people in carrying out the just cause of 
defending and building their socialist fatherland in the north, 
in trying to reunify the country through peaceful means, and in 
struggling to turn the Korean peninsula into a zone of peace and 
stability and free from nuclear weapons. 
  We, the Lao people, wish the official friendship visit to 
the 
LPDR by Comrade Kang Song-san, premier of the DPRK 
Administrative Council, and his party success, thereby 
contributing to further strengthening the relations of 
friendship and cooperation between the LPDR and the DPRK. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

