<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Premier, Delegation Visit Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Premier, Delegation Visit Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Khamtai </H4>

<F P=102> BK0306160694 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0306160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This afternoon at the Prime Minister's Office in 
Vientiane, His Excellency [H.E.] Khamtai Siphandon, and H.E. 
Kang Song-san, premier of the Administrative Council of the 
DPRK, held official talks. 
  Attending the talks on the Lao side were Khamphoui 
Keoboualapha, deputy prime minister and chairman of the 
Committee for Planning and Cooperation; Somsavat Lengsavat, 
foreign affairs minister; Bouason Boupphavan, deputy minister 
attached to the Prime Minister's Office; Thongvan Phanlatsavong, 
deputy minister of trade; Ponmek Dalaloi, Lao ambassador 
extraordinary and plenipotentiary to the DPRK; and a number of 
technical officials. 
  Attending the talks on the DPRK side were Kong Chin-tae, 
vice 
premier; Yi Song-tae, chairman of the State External Economic 
Affairs Committee; Jo Kyu-il, deputy foreign affairs minister; 
Chong Song-nam and Choe Bong-su, vice chairmen of the State 
External Economic Affairs Committee; and Chang Yong-chun, DPRK 
ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary to Laos. 
  At the talks, which lasted nearly two hours, the two sides 
informed each other on their respective internal situations and 
the confusing changes in the international situation. They 
reviewed the bilateral relations of the past and during the 
period of renovation. The two sides pledged to increase 
cooperation for mutual benefit. The talks were permeated with an 
atmosphere of intimacy and mutual understanding. 
  At 1700 Kang Song-san and his entourage paid a courtesy call 
on President Nouhak Phoumsavan at the Hokham Presidential Palace. 
  At 1900 today at the National Assembly hall, the prime 
minister will host a banquet in honor of the DPRK delegation. 

</TEXT>

