<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ramos Asks Indonesia To Release Fishermen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramos Asks Indonesia To Release Fishermen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0306134194 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0306134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] For its strong effort to stave off the holding of 
the Asia-Pacific Conference on East Timor in Manila, the Ramos 
administration is asking Indonesia to return the gesture. 
President Ramos is asking for the immediate release of some 90 
Filipino fishermen detained since last month in North Sulawesi. 
President Ramos expressed hope that Jakarta would accede to 
Manila's request. He evoked the phrase ASEAN cooperation and 
brotherhood, the same words he used to ban foreign delegates on 
the East Timor conference. 

</TEXT>

