<F P=103> BK0406121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok XING XIAN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Chuan Likphai warmly received Zheng 
Hongye, chairman of the China Council for the Promotion of 
International Trade, and his 16-member private trade delegation 
at the National Assembly yesterday afternoon. The prime 
minister also was photographed with the delegation. 
  Chuan warmly welcomed the delegation to Thailand. He said 
that the warm reception extended to him during his visit to 
China last August would be engraved in his memory forever. He 
is satisfied with the smooth implementation of the nine 
agreements and contacts signed during his visit. 
  Chuan said that many Thai businessmen were investing in 
China. He hoped that more Chinese entrepreneurs will invest in 
Thailand. He believed that the visit by the Chinese delegation 
would further promote friendly Sino-Thai relations. 
  Chief delegate Zheng Hongye expressed his heartfelt 
gratitude 
for the cordial audience granted by the prime minister, although 
he was very busy. He also seconded the prime minister's 
remarks. He said that amidst rapid economic growth in China, 
Chinese entrepreneurs are interested in more investment 
cooperation and development exchanges with their Thai 
counterparts. 

</TEXT>

