<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   KYODO Chief Meets With Do Muoi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KYODO Chief Meets With Do Muoi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0306154894 Hanoi VNA in English 1430 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0306154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 3 -- A delegation of KYODO NEWS 
SERVICE of Japan led by its President Yasuhiko Inukai who is 
also chairman of the Organization of Asia-Pacific News Agency 
(OANA) pays a working visit to Vietnam from May 31 to June 6, at 
the invitation of Mr Do Phuong, director general of Vietnam News 
Agency (VNA). 
  President Inukai and his entourage called on party General 
Secretary Do Muoi on June 2. 
  During the meeting, President Inukai said that he had 
honour to be received by and have cordial talks with party 
General Secretary Do Muoi. He expressed he rejoice [as 
received] over the successes of Vietnam's renovation with 
political stability, economic development and broaden 
international relations. 
  In a cordial atmosphere, party General Secretary Do Muoi 
expressed determination of the Vietnamese people in 
implementation of objectives of peace and stability at home and 
in the region as well as maintaining its national independence, 
overcome difficulties in order to build Vietnam into a country 
of prosperity and social equality and civilization. He stressed 
that the foreign policies of the Vietnamese party and state aim 
at broadening its cooperation with all countries, especially the 
countries in Asia. General Secretary Do Muoi expressed his 
welcome and wish the mutual cooperation and assistance between 
VIETNAM NEWS AGENCY and KYODO NEWS SERVICE be developed further 
in order to contribute their parts into peace, stability, 
cooperation and development of the two countries as well as 
Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole. 
  Earlier, President Inukai and his party were received by 
Vice Prime Minister Nguyen Khanh. During the meeting, Vice 
Prime Minister Nguyen Khanh highly valued cooperation between 
VIETNAM NEWS AGENCY and KYODO news over the past 20 years. He 
affirmed that the Vietnamese Government strongly supports VNA to 
participate OANA. 
  During its stay, the KYODO news delegation and the VNA 
leadership exchanged views in order to strengthen further 
cooperation between the two news agencies, especially in 
exchange of economic news in the current situation. 
  The KYODO news delegation paid floral tribute at the Ho Chi 
Minh mausoleum, visited his home and office and some cultural 
economic establishments in Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City, Quang 
Nam-Danang, Thua Thien-Hue and Vung Tau Provinces. 

</TEXT>

