<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vo Van Kiet Receives Jardine Matheson Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vo Van Kiet Receives Jardine Matheson Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0506155794 Hanoi VNA in English 1428 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0506155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 5 -- Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet 
received Saturday afternoon Mr S. Keswick, president of Jardine 
Matheson Holdings group, who arrived here on June 3 for a 
three-day visit to Vietnam. 
  P.M. Kiet appreciated the group's early presence in the 
country, and its desire for cooperation and investment in the 
construction of infrastructure in Vietnam. He expressed his 
hope that the cooperative relations between the two sides would 
continue to develop. 
  For his part, Mr Keswick briefed the Vietnamese prime 
minister of the results of Jardine Matheson Holdings' activities 
over the past four years, particularly in the fields of energy, 
infrastructure and coal exploitation. 
  He affirmed that the group's cooperation and investment in 
Vietnam would be further promoted in the coming years. He said 
he believed that Vietnam's open-door policies and its potentials 
would serve as firm foundation for the success of his group's 
investment and cooperation projects in conformity with both 
sides' interest. 

</TEXT>

