<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier of Australia's New South Wales Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Premier of Australia's New South Wales Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0306161094 Hanoi VNA in English 1422 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0306161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 3 -- A delegation from Australia's 
largest state New South Wales, led by its Premier John Fahey, 
has visited Vietnam since May 31 aimed at promoting the 
multi-faceted relations between the two sides. 
  While staying in Vietnam, the New South Wales' delegation, 
which was accompanied by several Australian major companies and 
businessmen, was received today by Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet. 
  It had working sessions with Minister of Trade Le Van Triet 
on steps to expand the commercial and economic ties between 
Vietnam and Australia in general and New South Wales in 
particular. 
  It also had working sessions with the ministries of science, 
technology and environment, public health, energy, the State 
Committee for Cooperation and Investment and other institutions 
concerned, and the People's Committee of Quang Nam-Danang 
Province. The delegation called at several economic 
establishments, including the State Electric Control Centre and 
the National Optical Centre. At these meetings, both sides 
compared notes on how to further promote their bilateral 
relations. 
  It is scheduled to leave Vietnam on June 4. 

</TEXT>

