<H4>    3 Jun Afternoon </H4>

<F P=102> BK0306150294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0306150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Assembly deputies held a plenary 
meeting this afternoon in the Ba Dinh Conference Hall under the 
direction of National Assembly Vice Chairman Nguyen Ha Phan. 
  At the beginning of the meeting, Minister Do Quoc Sam, 
chairman of the State Planning Commission, on behalf of the 
government, read a report on the draft law on the promotion of 
domestic investment. Then, Nguyen Thanh Phong, vice chairman of 
the Economic and State Budget Committee, read an investigative 
report on the draft law on the promotion of domestic investment. 
  Also at the sitting, National Defense Minister Doan Khue, on 
behalf of the government, read a report on the revised draft law 
on military obligations. Then, Pham Loi, vice chairman of the 
National Defense and Security Committee, read an investigative 
report on the revised draft law on military obligations. 
  The National Assembly deputies will continue their work in 
the conference hall tomorrow, 4 June. 

</TEXT>

