<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Assembly Proceedings Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Assembly Proceedings Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Communique No. 9 Issued </H4>

<F P=102> BK0406154394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Fifth Session of the Ninth National Assembly 
issues Communique No. 9 as follows: 
  On the morning of 4 June, the National Assembly debated in 
the conference hall the draft law on the amendment of and 
supplement to a number of articles on the law on military 
service under the direction of National Assembly Vice Chairman 
Dang Quan Thuy. 
  Twenty-one deputies, out of the 41 registered to address the 
meeting, expressed their views. They were Ho Duc Duyet of Song 
Be, Tang Nghia of Ha Tinh, Tran Van Lien of Kien Giang, Vu Thi 
Ngoc Dau of Thai Binh, Nguyen Khoa Kim Boi of Thua Thien-Hue, 
Nguyen Van An of Ho Chi Minh City, Nguyen Dinh Hong of An Giang, 
Lo Van Inh of Lai Chau, K'Tuat of Lam Dong, Nguyen Quoc Thuoc of 
Nghe An, Dinh Van The of Vinh Phu, Lo Thi Luyen of Son La, 
Truong Cong Pho of Tien Giang, Duong Cong Suu of Lang Son, Tran 
Thi Bach Tuyet of Dong Nai, Tran Duc Tam of Ha Bac, Ha Quang Du 
of Tuyen Quang, Nguyen Don of Quang Nam-Da Nang, Chu Duy Kinh of 
Hanoi, Nguyen Viet Hong of Minh Hai, and Dam Van Nguy of Cao 
Bang. 
  The deputies held that the draft law has been carefully 
compiled and revised. It has received considerable input from 
people of all strata, National Assembly deputies, and different 
echelons and levels in the entire country. 
  The deputies concentrated their discussion on the following 
issues: the obligation and responsibility of mass organizations 
and economic organizations in the implementation of the law on 
military service; members and the duties of the military service 
council; postponement and exemption of military service in 
peacetime; the service terms in peacetime for non-commissioned 
officers and soldiers; rewards, punishments, and social justice 
in the execution of the law on military service; and regulations 
and policies regarding soldiers who have completed their 
military service. 
  In the afternoon, the deputies exchanged views in their 
groups about the draft law on the promotion of domestic 
investment in order to prepare for their debate on this draft 
law in the conference hall on 6 June. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

