<H3> <TI>   DPRK `Source' Says IAEA Inspections Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK `Source' Says IAEA Inspections Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0406025894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 4 Jun 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0406025894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Akio Tamesada; from NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 4 Jun Morning </F>
Edition] 
  [Text] Vienna, 2 Jun--In reference to the conclusion 
reached by the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) on 2 
June that effective inspection of fuel rods in experimental 
reactors has become impossible, a DPRK (North Korea) source in 
Vienna on 3 June once again insisted that the fuel rods taken 
out by North Korea are being stored in "a way to make future 
IAEA inspections possible." 
  The North Korean source said the IAEA was informed of this 
in 
a letter dated 2 June. 

</TEXT>

