<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 6 June Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] On the evening of 5 June, Prime Minister Tsutomu 
Hata commented on the trilateral discussions among Japan, the 
United States, and the ROK on the DPRK's (North Korea) suspected 
development of nuclear weapons. He said: "Japan needs to watch 
future developments calmly," indicating he intends to maintain a 
wait-and-see attitude. 
  He also said: "North Korea's statements are quite elusive 
[bimyo]. It seems to want to continue dialogue with the United 
States," giving his opinion that North Korea is still searching 
for a solution through talks with the United States. 
  The prime minister gave the above remarks in response to 
questions from reporters at his official residence. 

</TEXT>

