<H3> <TI>   Kakizawa Urges Arms Reduction Clause in NPT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kakizawa Urges Arms Reduction Clause in NPT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0506123694 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 4 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0506123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa spoke in connection 
with the extension of the nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT) 
at the House of Representatives' Foreign Affairs Committee on 3 
June, and said the government will call for addition to the 
treaty of a clause requiring specific actions for nuclear arms 
reductions by the nuclear nations. He said, "We will ask for 
inclusion in the treaty of provisions clearly requiring nuclear 
nations to reduce their nuclear arms." 

</TEXT>

