<F P=102>   SK0506083194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0814 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0506083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Grave Threat to Peace on Korean Peninsula" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The United States and 
the South Korean puppets announced that they would stage Ulchi 
Focus Lens joint military exercises in South Korea for two weeks 
from August 22 allegedly to fill the "gap" till the start of the 
"Team Spirit" war game. 
  The new large-scale nuclear war drill projected by the 
United 
States and the South Korean puppets is a grave challenge to the 
whole nation which desire peace on the Korean peninsula and its 
peaceful reunification, and it is a dangerous action to carry 
the situation on the Korean peninsula to the brink of war, 
declares NODONG SINMUN in a commentary today. 
  The analyst says: 
  The open announcement of the plan of a provocative war 
gamble 
against the North by the South Korean puppets together with 
outside forces clearly indicates that they do not want a 
solution to the peace problem on the Korean peninsula through 
dialogue and negotiation but seek to attain their aim of 
aggression with "strength". 
  The talk about "gap" is a poor excuse invented by them to 
justify the adventurous war racket against the North. 
  With nothing can the United States and the Kim Yong-sam 
group 
justify the Ulchi Focus Lens joint military exercises which 
would gravely threaten our nation and endanger peace in Asia and 
the rest of the world. 
  Our people who love peace do not want war but are never 
afraid of it and can never tolerate the aggressors provoking us. 
  The United States and the South Korean puppets must cancel 
the plan of an adventurous war gamble, pondering over the 
consequences to be entailed by their provocative play with fire. 

</TEXT>

