<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperative Farms Finish Rice Transplanting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperative Farms Finish Rice Transplanting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0406105394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1040 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0406105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 4 (KCNA) -- The cooperative farms 
across the country have finished rice-transplanting in all paddy 
fields except northern highland and cold areas and some rice 
seedling beds. 
  The agricultural working people have made a breakthrough for 
reaping another rich crop this year by finishing rice 
transplanting in the time most opportune for the highest yield. 
  Weeding has already entered a full-scale stage in Paechon, 
Chaeryong and Anak, South Hwanghae Province, and in Unjon, 
Chongju and Yomju, North Pyongan Province, and many other areas 
on the west coast. 
  Cooperative farms are pulling their full weight on manuring 
and tending crops. 

</TEXT>

