<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportedly Drafting Declaration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportedly Drafting Declaration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0506005094 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0000 GMT 5 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0506005094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [AFP, YONHAP From Vienna] </F>
  [Text] According to diplomats in Vienna, the Board of 
Governors of the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] has 
convened a special meeting to discuss a draft declaration urging 
North Korea to accept all inspections in relation to nuclear 
weapons development. 
  The diplomats said that the meeting, which was held a day 
before the official Board of Governors meeting scheduled for 5 
June, reviewed a draft declaration denouncing North Korea for 
violating the inspections provisions of the Nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT] by removing fuel rods from the 
five-megawatt experimental reactor without IAEA supervision. 
  They said that the declaration urges North Korea to fulfill 
the obligations of the NPT and that the declaration will be 
announced as an official result of the Board of Governors 
meeting or a president's statement. 
  The IAEA Board of Governors is expected to discuss the North 
Korean issue on 9 or 10 June when the UN Security Council makes 
a decision on sanctions against North Korea. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

