<F P=103> SK0506042194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It was learned that Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae 
and U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry used a hotline for 
about 30 minutes on the morning of 4 June to discuss 
preparations to strengthen ROK-U.S. joint military rapport in 
connection with the tense situation surrounding the Korean 
peninsula due to the North Korean nuclear issue. 
  A high-ranking Defense Ministry official revealed: "It is 
known that they discussed the issue from various angles on ways 
to make preparations to strengthen the military rapport between 
the two countries for possible provocations by North Korea if 
economic sanctions are imposed." This is the first time that 
the two ministers talked over the hotline, with the exception of 
the test conducted when it was installed last month. 

