<H3> <TI>   Opposition Party Caucus Resolution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Party Caucus Resolution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0406054594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0200 GMT 4 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0406054594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Party [DP] held a party caucus at the 
National Assembly building this morning and adopted a resolution 
urging North Korea to stop the nuclear fuel rod replacement 
operation immediately, ensure the nuclear transparency, and 
return to the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT]. 
  In the resolution, the DP noted that the present situation 
surrounding the North Korean nuclear issue is very grave and 
stressed that North Korea should fully allow the special 
inspection of the undeclared sites by the International Atomic 
Energy Agency. The DP also urged the government to make 
independent efforts in close cooperation with the United Nations 
and the four neighboring major powers, including the United 
States, to prevent war on the Korean peninsula. The DP also 
called on the United States and the United Nations to do their 
best to maintain dialogue for the peaceful settlement rather 
than resorting to the measures that could result in war. 

</TEXT>

