<H3> <TI>   Ruling Party Holds Meeting 4 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ruling Party Holds Meeting 4 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0406060394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0200 GMT 4 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0406060394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Liberal Party [DLP] held a meeting of 
senior party post holders today and discussed measures the party 
should take as the national security is driven into a tense 
situation while international sanctions against the North is 
impending because of the North Korean rejection of nuclear 
inspections. In the meeting, the DLP decided to make efforts to 
have the people become aware of the present security situation. 
  At today's meeting, Yi Se-ki, chairman of the Policy 
Committee, said that the crisis situation resulting from the 
North Korean nuclear issue is heightened because North Korea 
claimed that it would regard any form of sanctions against it as 
an act of war declaration against North Korea. Yi also said 
that in case the UN sanctions turn out to be difficult because 
of the Chinese opposition, despite the fact that measures for 
sanctions are pushed ahead on the part of the United Nations, 
the government is grouping for multinational sanctions among the 
ROK, Japan, and the United States. 
  DLP Chairman Kim Chong-pil noted this is the time for the 
people to be precisely aware of the national security situation, 
and stressed the need for the authorities to explain the present 
situation to the people and have them share the correct 
awareness. Chairman Kim Chong-pil stressed that the DLP should 
play a leading role in this. 

</TEXT>

