<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam Schedules Briefing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Yong-sam Schedules Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0606055894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0550 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0606055894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 6 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
will invite leaders of the three branches of government, the 
ruling Democratic Liberal Party and the opposition Democratic 
Party to a luncheon at Chongwadae [presidential offices] 
Wednesday to brief them on the results of his visit to Russia 
and discuss suprapartisan action on North Korea's nuclear 
program. 
  Kim will explain the latest developments concerning the 
North's nuclear ambitions and urge the attendees to make 
suprapartisan efforts to cope with any contingencies that 
international sanctions against Pyongyang might entail, informed 
sources in the ruling camp said Monday. 
  Opposition Democratic Party Chairman Yi Ki-taek, in the 
meantime, is expected to stress the need to solve the problem 
peacefully on the basis of his party's position that war should 
not break out under any circumstances. 
  The opposition leader is also likely to urge that sanctions, 
if deemed inevitable, should not be initiated by only three 
countries -- South Korea, the United States and Japan -- but by 
the United Nations as a whole. 

</TEXT>

