<H3> <TI>   DPRK Urged To Send Delegate to MAC Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Urged To Send Delegate to MAC Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0606053794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0531 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0606053794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 6 (YONHAP) -- The U.N. Command called on 
North Korea Monday to send a delegate to the official meeting of 
senior secretaries of the Military Armistice Commission [MAC] to 
discuss its recent unilateral withdrawal from MAC, the command 
said. 
  The command, citing clause 61 of the Armistice Agreement 
which stipulates that any changes require the consent of the two 
sides' commanders, noted that the commander of the U.N. forces 
has not concurred with North Korea's unilateral alteration of 
the agreement. 

</TEXT>

