<H3> <TI>   U.S., ROK Stage Air Strike Exercises 1, 2 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S., ROK Stage Air Strike Exercises 1, 2 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0406045294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0406045294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 4 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
mobilized nuclear-capable F-16 and F-15 fighter-bombers, 
pursuit-assault planes, VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] 
assault planes, electronic jamming planes and early warning 
planes based overseas and warplanes of the U.S. Airforce 
stationed in South Korea and the South Korean puppet Airforce, 
some 500 in all, in surprise air strike exercises against the 
North in the skies above Yongwol, Tanyang, Umsong and Asan Bay 
of South Korea on June 1 and 2, according to military sources. 
  Meanwhile, the South Korean puppets fired more than 500 
large-calibre machinegun and automatic rifle bullets, charging 
toward the Military Demarcation Line from Paju County on June 1. 
Formations of helicopter gunboats and transport helicopters 
staged ground-attack support and airlifting exercises in the 
skies above Pochon, Yonchon and Chorwon and Inje, South Korean 
Kangwon Province, on June 2. 
  Facts clearly show how desperately the U.S. imperialists and 
the South Korean puppets are trying to increase their combat 
capacity in a war against the North. 

</TEXT>

