<H3> <TI>   Malaysia LNG To Supply Sendai City With Gas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Malaysia LNG To Supply Sendai City With Gas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   942A0279B Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 28 May 94 p 
2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 942A0279B </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] Sendai City, which is proceeding with a conversion 
program from city gas to LNG (liquefied natural gas), announced 
on 27 May that it has concluded sales negotiations on LNG with 
Malaysia LNG Company. The formal signing will be Kuala Lumpur in 
the middle of July after they have received approval at a 
special municipal assembly session at the end of June. With 
prospects good for securing the raw material, the city will 
start on construction of a receiving base in Sendai harbor, 
aiming at introduction of LNG in 1997. 
  The details of the "confirmation of intent" that will be the 
premise of the sales contract agreed between Sendai city and 
Malaysia LNG are 1) the contract period will be for a 20-year 
period beginning in 1997, and the total import amount will be 
2.9 million tons; 2) Malaysia LNG will build a special tanker 
and Sendai city will assume the obligation for that; and 3) the 
place for transfer of the LNG will be the base in Sendai harbor. 
The formal sales contract that will determine the price, etc., 
will be concluded within the next one to two years. 
  The Sendai city LNG introduction program is the conversion 
of 
city gas, which supplies 356,000 households, from butane to LNG; 
total project costs such as for construction of the receiving 
base will be 85.8 billion yen. It initially had studied a method 
of receiving domestically produced LNG from Niigata by pipeline, 
but ultimately chose the tanker from overseas method and 
proceeded in negotiations with Malaysia LNG as the importer. 

</TEXT>

