<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion in Zamboanga City Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion in Zamboanga City Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Operation Against Abu Sayyaf </H4>

<F P=102> BK0306143094 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0306143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Earlier this morning government troops launched 
intensified land, air, and sea strikes against the Abu Sayyaf 
group in the village of Lumbahan in Patikul, Sulu. 
  This was announced today by Jericho Kagawan, Philippine 
National Police [PNP] director for operations. He explained 
that the operation was a result of the group's continued refusal 
to stop their illegal activities. 
  The group is behind the series of kidnap-for-ransom cases in 
different parts of Mindanao. Negotiations were conducted with 
the group on stopping these activities, but they fell on deaf 
ears. 
  According to Kagawan, three Marine battalions supported by 
the PNP are currently sweeping down on the areas where the 
bandits are hiding. 

</TEXT>

