<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion in Zamboanga City Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion in Zamboanga City Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Abu Sayyaf Responsible </H4>

<F P=102> BK0706044894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0706044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Abu Sayyaf extremist group has claimed 
responsibility for the Sunday bombing at the commercial center 
in Zamboanga City in southern Philippines. Xeroxed letters 
reportedly from a certain Abu Jihad were delivered by an 
unidentified youth yesterday afternoon. 
  Thirty-six people were wounded in the bomb blast. The 
explosive was believed planted inside or beneath a car parked 
beside Shopper Central. The car was a total wreck. The 
explosion was so powerful, it was heard by residents within a 
five kilometer radius. 

</TEXT>

