  [Text] A Communist Party of Vietnam delegation led by 
Central Committee member Nguyen Van Hon visited Cuba from 30 May 
to 3 June. The delegation had visited a number of other Latin 
American countries earlier. 
  Comrade Juan Almeida, member of the Cuban Communist Party 
Central Committee Political Bureau in charge of ideological work 
and foreign relations, received and held cordial talks with the 
Vietnamese delegation. Comrades Almeida and Nguyen Van Hon 
asserted the Cuban and Vietnamese parties and governments' 
aspiration to strengthen and develop the relations of friendship 
and cooperation between the two countries. 

