<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Businessmen in Russia Sign Labor Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Businessmen in Russia Sign Labor Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3105060994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3105060994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A reporter of the VIETNAM NEWS AGENCY based in 
Moscow reveals that on 27 May, Russia's Federal Immigration 
Agency and the Vietnamese Businessmen Association in Russia 
signed a cooperation agreement on the employment of foreign 
workers in Russia and Vietnam. 
  According to the agreement, Russia's Federal Immigration 
Agency and (?Vinencaso) will help each other in resolving issues 
such as attracting and employing Russian and Vietnamese workers 
in their respective countries. 
  (?Vinencaso) will cooperate with the Russia's Federal 
Immigration Agency to create conditions to attract and employ 
Russian and Vietnamese workers in companies and enterprises 
which Vietnam businessmen helped to build up. The Russia's 
Federal Immigration Agency will help (?Vinencaso) find 
Vietnamese workers for enterprises that are operating or in the 
process of rebuilding in Russia, and will send Russian workers 
to Vietnamese enterprises and agencies upon the request of 
(?Vinencaso). 
  This agreement does not affect other agreements signed in 
this field between the Russian and Vietnamese state authorities. 

</TEXT>

