<H3> <TI>   Daily: ROK `Brutally Suppressed' Demonstrators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily: ROK `Brutally Suppressed' Demonstrators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0406052494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0455 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0406052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Sword-brandishing of Nuclearmaniac" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 4 (KCNA) -- The Kim Yong-sam fascist 
clique a few days ago brutally suppressed inhabitants in Uljin 
County in a demonstration against the building of a nuclear 
waste dump, leaving some 20 people mortally wounded and 
arresting 24 on the scene. 
  NODONG SINMUN today says this brutality can be committed 
only 
by such fascist tyrants as the Kim Yong-sam group whose mode of 
existence is sword-brandishing. 
  To maintain one's existence and protect living environments 
pertains to the intrinsic independent rights of human beings, 
the analyst says, and continues: 
  The exercise of these rights can never be criminalized or 
suppressed in any case. Nevertheless, the puppets are brutally 
suppressing the people's righteous struggle for existence at the 
point of the bayonet. This is really a fascist outrage fully 
revealing the ferocity of the "civilian" dictatorship. 
  Their suppression of people opposing the building of a 
nuclear waste dump is a brigandish act for forcing them to 
reconcile themselves to nuclear harm. 
  Unpardonable is the crime of the Kim Yong-sam group which is 
going to build a nuclear waste dump and inflict irrevocable 
nuclear disasters upon the people, after converting South Korea 
into a nuclear base of the United States. 

</TEXT>

