<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Contacts UNSC Representatives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Contacts UNSC Representatives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0706000494 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2100 GMT 6 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0706000494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP report from UN Headquarters] </F>
  [Text] ROK Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu, who is visiting 
New York, held consecutive individual contacts with 
representatives of the permanent member states of the UN 
Security Council [SC] on 6 June to discuss cooperation on 
sanction measures on North Korea. 
  Minister Han explained the ROK Government's position that 
sanctions on North Korea are inevitable and exchanged views with 
representatives of the UN Security Council permanent member 
states regarding the objective, timing, and methods of 
sanctions. Particularly, Minister Han reportedly asked for 
cooperation in implementing sanctions on North Korea during his 
meetings with Representatives Li Zhaoxing of the PRC and 
Vorontsov of Russia. 
  A high-ranking official of the ROK mission to the United 
Nations said that the UN Security Council is likely to adopt a 
sanction resolution rather than a warning resolution and that 
the United States will lead discussions on sanction measures 
sometime this week. 

</TEXT>

