<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   President: I Will Deter North From Nuclear Bomb </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President: I Will Deter North From Nuclear Bomb </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0606121994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1153 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0606121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tashkent, June 6 (YONHAP) -- South Korean President 
Kim Yong-sam said on Monday that North Korea's nuclear 
development is a matter of life and death, which threatens world 
peace as well as the 70 million Korean people. He told 
journalists before he leaves Uzbekistan on Monday that if North 
Korea dares to push for imprudent adventure, then it will lead 
to nothing but self-destruction of North Korea. 
  Kim said, "We cannot allow even half a nuclear weapon in 
North Korea. I will deter North Korea without fail from having 
a nuclear weapon. We are watching the move of North Korea 24 
hours a day, and the military power of South Korea, U.S. forces 
in Korea and United Nations force can repress war on the Korean 
peninsula." 
  But he added that there are no strange military moves now in 
North Korea. "I will have the national security conference 
according to Constitution on Wednesday at Chongwadae. I will 
also have a dialogue with U.S. President Bill Clinton over the 
telephone to discuss ways to cope with the North Korean nuclear 
problem as soon as I return home," he said. 

</TEXT>

