<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK UN Envoy Confirms Missile Test Firing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK UN Envoy Confirms Missile Test Firing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0606232394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2100 GMT 6 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0606232394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP Report from Geneva] </F>
  [Text] North Korea made it clear yesterday hat it had test 
fired a missile in the East Sea, stressing that it was a routine 
exercise. 
  In a news conference, (Han Cha-won), North Korea's permanent 
representative to the United Nations, said that the test firing 
of the missile was a regular and routine exercise and that North 
Korea's missiles are completely for defensive purposes. 
  The Japanese and U.S. Governments revealed at the end of 
last 
month that North Korea had tested a missile -- an improved model 
of China's Silk Worm missiles. 
  Until now, North Korea has not confirmed that it had test 
fired a missile. 

</TEXT>

