<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 7 KYODO -- Trade Minister Eijiro Hata 
said Tuesday [7 Jun] that the Japanese economy has been showing 
some bright signals and predicted there is little chance of it 
sagging again. 
  Hata, minister of international trade and industry, told a 
regular press conference after a cabinet meeting that he is 
paying especially close attention to consumer-spending-related 
economic indicators such as sales at department stores and 
supermarkets. 
  Hata's remarks followed the latest official economic 
diagnosis issued by the Economic Planning Agency earlier in the 
day, which said some bright signs are visible in Japan's economy 
despite overall sluggishness. 

</TEXT>

